It borders Bavaria (Germany) in the north, the Kufstein and Schwaz districts in the west, and the Pinzgau region (Salzburg) in the east and south. It has an area of 1,163.06 km². As of 2012, 61,966 people lived there. The administrative center of the district is Kitzbühel. == Places == The district has 20 municipalities, one of them is a town, and three of them are market towns. === Towns === # Kitzbühel === Market towns === # Fieberbrunn # Hopfgarten im Brixental # Sankt Johann in Tirol === Municipalities === # Aurach bei Kitzbühel # Brixen im Thale # Going am Wilden Kaiser # Hochfilzen # Itter # Jochberg # Kirchberg in Tirol # Kirchdorf in Tirol # Kössen # Oberndorf in Tirol # Reith bei Kitzbühel # Sankt Jakob in Haus # Sankt Ulrich am Pillersee # Schwendt # Waidring # Westendorf Category:Districts of Tyrol (state)
